# Playwright Login Automation Framework

A clean, maintainable test automation framework built with **Playwright** and **JavaScript**, implementing the **Page Object Model (POM)** design pattern. 

This project automates login validation scenarios against the Practice Test Automation login page.

## Key Features
* **Page Object Model (POM):** Clean separation of page selectors/actions from the actual test assertions.
* **Auto-Waiting:** Fully utilizes Playwright's native auto-waiting mechanisms to eliminate flaky, hardcoded timeouts.
* **Centralized Configuration:** Crucial configurations (like `baseURL` and browser selection) are managed in a single `config/config.js` file.

---

## Tech Stack & Tools
* **Language:** JavaScript (Node.js)
* **Automation Engine:** Playwright
* **Version Control:** Git & GitHub

---

## Setup & Installation

Follow these steps to run the tests locally on your machine:

### 1. Prerequisites
Make sure you have [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) installed.

### 2. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone [https://github.com/Debbie012/Part4_Automation-Testing.git](https://github.com/Debbie012/Part4_Automation-Testing.git)
cd Part4_Automation-Testing